The SA Football Association (Safa) is facing a R7.6m lawsuit by a marketing company over nonpayment of services rendered in the broadcast rights deal signed between Safa and SABC worth R110m. SS Network, a marketing firm based in Joburg, filed summons at the South Gauteng high court on Thursday stating that the football body was playing hide and seek with its payment despite receiving payments of more than R100m from the SABC during the period between May 1 2017 and April 30 2018. TO READ MORE ON THIS STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY' S SUNDAY WORLD.